        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>screaming terror is like mez. higher the charisma, the better chance of landing<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote>Urban legend.  There is absolutely no relation between Charisma and ST.  In fact, Charisma is completely meaningless to necros (except for lowering vendor prices).<BR><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=2 face="Verdana" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>ST has a set duration of ummm, not long, maybe 20 secs or so. It does not wear off early and pets can no longer break the mez. <hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana" size=2 id=quote>No.  ST has a <b>maximum</b> duration of 18 seconds.  It can and will break early (usually at the most inconvinent time).  Just like any mezz, attacking the target will automatically break it.  Also, pets will automatically back off (and refuse to re-engage) a mezzed target.</P><P></P><P><BR>--Nergal Teir'Draconis, Children of the Phoenix (Tunare)<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
