        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Yup, Sally is right. ST, if it lands, is a guaranteed 18 seconds (time it if you like, though admittedly it 'feels' like less sometimes.. it only feels it though). It's not based off of CHA (I can't prove this, aside from having played the game from beta and being a Warlock now) but I've had 150 CHA, and I've had 10 CHA. Made no difference to Screaming Terror what so ever. 18 seconds everytime it lands. Yes, it is based off Magic resist. If a mob is resistant to Magic, it may not land. At level 60 however, ST is a very useful thing. In fact it's in my second spell slot of my 'generally memmed' spells. The most I can hold (that can be held for that matter, due to recast time and spell duration) is 2 mobs at once, and then fight a third. That can get hair as 1 resist on an ST will mess up your rhythem, but for your average level 45-55 mob, I'd say you get resisted maybe 1 out of 25 times when you're level 60. So it's usually a safe spell to count on. Use it and groups will appreciate your prowess with it. Don't use it and you're simply missing out on part of the Necro arsenal of abilities. Happy gaming.</P><P></P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205091" target="_blank"><font color=red><font size=5>Ashtaroth Solarium</font id=size5></font id=red></a><BR><i>Nec-Romancer of Innoruuk</i><BR><i>Legends of the Realm</i><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

